ar</span><span>, </span></li><li><span class="hlFld-ContribAuthor">Sindhu Kumar</span><span>, </span></li><li><span class="hlFld-ContribAuthor">Sai Swarupa Reddy Vulasala</span><span>, </span></li><li><span class="hlFld-ContribAuthor">Chidi Nwachukwu</span><span>, </span></li><li><span class="hlFld-ContribAuthor">Sanjay Lamsal</span></li></ul></div><div class="meta">17 August 2022 | Journal of Clinical Imaging Science, Vol. 12</div></div><div class="getFTR external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.25259/JCIS_70_2022">Crossref</a></div></div></li><li class="citedByEntry" data-doi="10.1016/B978-0-323-70849-4.00050-5"><div class="related"><div class="related__title"><a target="_blank" href="https://doi.org/10.1016/B978-0-323-70849-4.00050-5">Buckle up: Abdominal trauma</a></div><div class="related__authors"><ul class="rlist--inline loa mobile-authors loa-height"><li><span class="hlFld-ContribAuthor">Robert Vezzetti</span></li></ul></div><div class="meta">2022Jan1</div></div><div class="getFTR external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/B978-0-323-70849-4.00050-5">Crossref</a></div></div></li><li class="citedByEntry" data-doi="10.1038/s41598-020-80408-9"><div class="related"><div class="related__title"><a target="_blank" href="https://doi.org/10.1038/s41598-020-80408-9">Phenotyping placental oxygenation in Lgals1 deficient mice using 19F MRI</a></div><div class="related__authors"><ul class="rlist--inline loa mobile-authors loa-height"><li><span class="hlFld-ContribAuthor">Philipp Boehm-Sturm</span><span>, </span></li><li><span class="hlFld-ContribAuthor">Susanne Mueller</span><span>, </span></li><li><span class="hlFld-ContribAuthor">Nancy Freitag</span><span>, </span></li><li><span class="hlFld-ContribAuthor">Sophia Borowski</span><span>, </span></li><li><span class="hlFld-ContribAuthor">Marco Foddis</span><span>, </span></li><li><span class="hlFld-ContribAuthor">Stefan P. Koch</span><span>, </span